Merge pull request #31 from kinoru/iso8601-z

Add zero UTC offset (Z) support to ISO 8601 format

Add zero UTC offset (Z) support to ISO 8601 format

Previously, the documentation said it could parse time strings in the
ISO 8601 format, and gave two examples:

- 2014-04-05T17:25:04+00:00
- 2014-04-05T17:25:04Z

Unfortunately the support for the latter was not there yet, because the
`Format_TzHM_Colon` constructor of `TimeFormatElem` could not handle the
character "Z", the zero UTC offset zone designator in ISO 8601.

This commit leaves the `Format_TzHM_Colon` constructor as is for
backwards compatibility, and adds a new constructor
`Format_TzHM_Colon_Z` which first attempts to parse "Z" and falls back
to `Format_TzHM_Colon`. Then it changes the `TimeFormat` instance of
`ISO8601_DateAndTime` to give it the proper capability to parse the
second example.

As far as I can tell, this is a backwards compatible change.

(Hopefully) Solves #30.

Merge pull request #26 from zenhack/daysInMonth

Fix exposure of daysInMonth, and make use of it in the tests.

Use newly exposed daysInMonth to tighten up tests.

* Extend Arbitrary Date instance to cover all days in month
* Make isValidDate more strict (e.g. day 31 of November is not valid)
* Add a basic QuickCheck property to test the arbitrary instance.

This also tightens up the definition of isValidDate
